---
title: Santorini Style Tomatokeftedes with Homemade Tzatziki and Lemon, Green Bean & Baby Leaf Salad
description: Tomatokeftedes are a typical Greek appetiser - small tomato croquettes originating from the Cyclades. The intense flavour comes from tomatoes grown without water in the natural volcanic soils of the area. These croquettes or fritters are mixed with Greek style salad cheese, onion and parsley before being fried in hot oil for a crispy outside.
